Now let's take it for a spin. Creating a container from it (again, with the --rm option), asking for the Bash shell, shows us this, where we move from the command line prompt on the host (mine here is a simple ";") to the command line prompt inside the container ("root âžœ / $"):<BR />
<PRE><CODE>; <STRONG>docker run --rm -it tut-image-test bash</STRONG><BR />
root âžœ / $</CODE></PRE><BR />
